1 Section 1. Section 60-6,257, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 60-6,257 (1) It shall be unlawful for a person to drive a motor
4 vehicle required to be registered in this state upon a highway:
5 (a) If the windows in such motor vehicle are tinted so that the
6 driver's clear view through the windshield or side or rear windows is
7 reduced or the ability to see into the motor vehicle is substantially
8 impaired;
9 (b) If the windshield has any sunscreening material that is not
10 clear and transparent below the AS-1 line or if it has a sunscreening
11 material that is red, yellow, or amber in color above the AS-1 line;
12 (c) If the front side windows have any sunscreening or other
13 transparent material that has a luminous reflectance of more than twenty
14 thirty-five percent or has light transmission of less than twenty thirty-
15 five percent;
16 (d) If the rear window or side windows behind the front seat have
17 sunscreening or other transparent material that has a luminous
18 reflectance of more than twenty thirty-five percent or has light
19 transmission of less than twenty percent except for the rear window or
20 side windows behind the front seat on a multipurpose vehicle, van, or
21 bus; or
22 (e) If the windows of a camper, motor home, pickup cover, slide-in
23 camper, or other motor vehicle do not meet the standards for safety
24 glazing material specified by federal law in 49 C.F.R. 571.205.
25 (2) For purposes of this section and sections 60-6,258 and 60-6,259:
26 (a) AS-1 line shall mean a line extending from the letters AS-1,
27 found on most motor vehicle windshields, running parallel to the top of
28 the windshield or shall mean a line five inches below and parallel to the
29 top of the windshield, whichever is closer to the top of the windshield;
30 (b) Camper shall mean a structure designed to be mounted in the
31 cargo area of a truck or attached to an incomplete vehicle with motive
