1 power for the purpose of providing shelter for persons;
2 (c) Glass-plastic glazing material shall mean a laminate of one or
3 more layers of glass and one or more layers of plastic in which a plastic
4 surface of the glazing faces inward when the glazing is installed in a
5 vehicle;
6 (d) Light transmission shall mean the ratio of the amount of total
7 light, expressed in percentages, which is allowed to pass through the
8 sunscreening or transparent material to the amount of total light falling
9 on the motor vehicle window;
10 (e) Luminous reflectance shall mean the ratio of the amount of total
11 light, expressed in percentages, which is reflected outward by the
12 sunscreening or transparent material to the amount of total light falling
13 on the motor vehicle window;
14 (f) Motor home shall mean a multipurpose passenger vehicle that
15 provides living accommodations;
16 (g) Multipurpose vehicle shall mean a motor vehicle designed to
17 carry ten or fewer passengers that is constructed on a truck chassis or
18 with special features for occasional off-road use;
19 (h) Pickup cover shall mean a camper having a roof and sides but
20 without a floor designated to be mounted on and removable from the cargo
21 area of a truck by the user;
22 (i) Slide-in camper shall mean a camper having a roof, floor, and
23 sides designed to be mounted on and removable from the cargo area of a
24 truck by the user; and
25 (j) Sunscreening material shall mean a film, material, tint, or
26 device applied to motor vehicle windows for the purpose of reducing the
27 effects of the sun.
28 Sec. 2. Original section 60-6,257, Reissue Revised Statutes of
29 Nebraska, is repealed.
